# Finding 052
- Severity: Medium
- Pattern type: AI slop; Billing constants duplicated across service and storage layers
- File + line(s): `packages/billing/billing-service-core/src/shared/constants.js:1-216`, `packages/billing/billing-knex-mysql/src/shared/constants.js:1-216`
- Why it can drift/fail: Core billing constants (statuses, failure codes, defaults, transitions) are duplicated across packages. If one changes (e.g., new status or default), the other will not update automatically.
- Concrete impact: Service logic and storage/repository logic can disagree about valid statuses or transitions, leading to inconsistent behavior or incorrect enforcement.
- Exact remediation: Extract a single `billing-constants` module used by both packages.

## Resolution
- Summary: moved billing constants into `@jskit-ai/billing-core` and re-exported explicit constants in billing-service-core and billing-knex-mysql to eliminate duplication.
